NOTE: Your PICK host must be in a mode ready to receive the data (in the insert mode of the editor or word processor; or the Mac-To-Host program supplied with your MacWise\'99 disk is running.)\
\
When using the PICK editor to receive your data, make sure your text file does not contain any blank lines. The editor will exit the insert mode as soon as it sees a blank line.\
\
When using a PICK word processor to receive the data, make sure that the hyphenation mode is turned off. If you leave hyphenation turned on, the word processor will stop and ask you to hyphenate a word during the data transfer and all of the data will not be transferred.\
