\f1\fs26 \cf0 Your MacWise\'99 disk has a file called 
\b MAC.TO.HOST PROGRAM
\b0 . This is a PICK BASIC program which you can transfer to your host computer. When compiled and run, it receives data from a Macintosh text file and puts it in a file called HOLD on your host computer. Each line received by the host from the Mac becomes a new item in the HOLD file.\

\fs30 \

\fs26 You don't need to type this program on your host computer. Just send it from your Mac to your host with the 
\b Mac-To-Host Transfer
\b0  option in MacWise\'99.\page 
